{title: An Empty Mansion}
{artist: Wilburn Brothers}
{composer: Written by C.A. Luttrell and Mrs. J.B. Karnes}

[3/4 time]
[C]Here I labor and toil as I [F]look for a [C]home
Just a humble abode among [G7]men
While in [C]Heaven a mansion is [F]waiting for [C]me
And a gentle voice [G7]pleading come [C]in
There's a mansion now empty just waiting for me
At the end of life's trouble some [G7]way
Many [C]friends and dear loved ones will [F]welcome me [C]there
Near the door of that [G7]mansion some[C]day
Ever thankful am I that my [F]Savior and [C]Lord
Promised unto the weary sweet [G7]rest
Nothing [C]more could I ask than a [F]mansion a[C]bove
There to live with [G7]saved and the [C]blessed
repeat #2